The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Lesbians flee from rebel captivity

 Kathmandu, April 10 (PTI): Two girls, who were detained by the Maoists for being lesbians, have escaped from captivity and approached human rights groups in Nepal seeking protection.

 Dukhani Choudhary, 16, and Sarita Choudhury, 22, were detained in Pakali village of Sunsari district on February 3 after the Maoists, who oppose same sex relationships, found out that the two were lesbians, said Sunil Babu Panta, president of Blue Diamond Society, a group dedicated to the welfare of lesbians and gay communities in Nepal. The Maoists local commander in Sunsari district in eastern Nepal kept the girls under his custody for one month with the help of Dukhanis family members, Panta said.




